==English==
===Etymology===
By analogy with a worm travelling from one side of an apple to the other through the apple rather than over its surface.

===Noun===
'''wormhole''' (''plural'' '''wormholes''')

#(''physics'') A [[hypothetical]] [[shortcut]] between distant parts of space and so potentially allowing [[faster-than-light]] travel and [[time travel]].

====Synonym====
*[[Einstein-Rosen bridge]] (''technical'')

